summary: 01/17/1993: The Hezb-e-Islami group attempted to shoot down two civilian airliners operated by Ariana Airlines in Kabul, Afghanistan. The group used rockets in this attack, with estimates of as many as 30 rockets falling in this incident. No one was injured and there was no damage.
target1: Two Civilian Planes Operated by Ariana Airlines
addnotes: The two airliners were leaving for Peshawar, Pakistan and New Delhi, India. Reports noted that some missiles might have also slammed into the grounds of the presidential palace in central Kabul; however, such reports were not confirmed.
scite1: “Afghan Rebels Target Airlines,” Press Association, January 17, 1993.
